caption.body: #OnThisDay in 1903, the Wright brothers successfully flew a heavier-than-air, mechanically propelled aircraft at Kitty Hawk, North Carolina.  In 1940, following years of significant advancements in aviation, President Franklin D. Roosevelt honored the Wright brothersâ€™ early achievement by issuing a proclamation designating December 17th as Pan American Aviation Day.  This commemoration encourages citizens from North, Central, and South America to increase their interest in aviation. #panamericanaviationday #wrightbrothers #wrightbrothersday #avgeek  Rendering of the Wright Brothers Flyer 1903 SFO Museum Collection Gift of United Airlines Archives 1999.047.219
